communications.subject: Tennessee Public Records Act Request: Untitled
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Tennessee Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Any open fire code violations currently on record for Main Street Flats, 101 S Main Street, Memphis, TN 38103. Thank you!

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 7 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Kent Hoover, a citizen of Tennessee, in coordination with Lindsey McQuiddy.

communications.subject: Illinois Freedom of Information Act. Request: Mail Scheme
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Illinois Freedom of Information Act., I hereby request the following records:

I hope this request finds you in good spirits.
I request that a copy of the following documents [or documents containing the following information] be provided to me that pertains to all prisons in Illinois:

All reports of incidents involving negative or positive results for testing of substances on incoming mail in the year 2024. 

I know that these documents exist because of the news report at  https://www.wsiltv.com/news/top-stories/multiple-incidents-reported-at-correctional-centers-in-illinois-recently/article_b743ad4c-713a-11ef-9c3b-734b1ee6bd83.html where documents are attached. The article states, "One report (attached below) was sent to News 3 from Senator Bryant. It stated an incident took place on August 16, 2024, at the Pinckneyville Correctional Center." The article also contains, "Another report Senator Bryant sent to News 3 was from Big Muddy River Correctional Center with the incident date of 7.11.24." 

In a later article, Senator Bryant claims she has 60 incident reports. I'm requesting all of these plus all the reports mentioned in the WSIL article:

Big Muddy River Correctional Center 7.11.24
Menard Correctional Center 8.27.24
Menard Correctional Center 8.28.24
Menard Correctional Center 8.29.24
Menard Correctional Center 8.30.24
Menard Correctional Center 9.1.24
Pinckneyville Correctional Center 9.2.24
Menard Correctional Center 9.2.24
Pinckneyville Correctional Center 9.3.24
Menard Correctional Center 9.3.24
Menard Correctional Center 9.4.24


In the event that there are fees, please inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request be filled electronically.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Ivan Glynn

title: 1990-2010 Documents Relating to Gifted and Talented Education curriculum, instructional materials, studies, and classwork/tests

communications.subject: California Public Records Act Request: 1990-2010 Documents Relating to Gifted and Talented Education curriculum, instructional materials, studies, and classwork/tests
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

I am looking for any and all documents that would include details of the curriculum, instructional materials, classwork, or tests that were given to public school students, as well as any studies that were published using data collected from the students in the Gifted and Talented Education program in public schools.

The range of dates i am interested is anything between 1990 and 2010.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

John Nordberg
